    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1882-12-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1882-12-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="522" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d522">
                <head>No. 523.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Heap</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Frelinghuysen</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Constantinople</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1882-12-03">
                            <hi rend="italic">December</hi> 3, 1882</date>.
                            (Received December 22.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 148.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>:* * * In reference to the case of Dr. Frederick
                        L. Kingsbury, mentioned in No. 33, dated the 16th of November last, I have
                        been informed, both by himself and Mr. Wyndham, the charge d’affaires of
                        Great Britain, that his difficulties with the Bulgarian authorities have
                        been satisfactorily arranged, and he has received permission to practice his
                        profession in the principality. This settlement has been effected through
                        the good offices of Mr. Lascelles, Her Majesty’s agent in Bulgaria, acting
                        under instructions from the Earl of Dufferin. I have requested Mr. Wyndham
                        to convey the thanks of this legation to Mr. Lascelles.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>G. H. HEAP.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
